Zwartowo  (German Schwartow) is a settlement in the administrative district of Gmina Grzmiąca, within Szczecinek County, West Pomeranian Voivodeship, in north-western Poland. It lies approximately  north-west of Szczecinek and  east of the regional capital Szczecin.
For the history of the region, see History of Pomerania.
